THE LONDON SEO PLAYBOOK 2026 — Meridian Digital Ltd

This 42-page tactical playbook distils everything Meridian's in-house SEO team uses to put London brands on page one of Google, inside AI Overviews, and cited by ChatGPT, Claude and Perplexity. It opens with a diagnostic of the London search landscape in 2026 — AI Overview penetration by query type, seasonality patterns that determine optimal publishing cadence, and the shifting click-through curves for borough-level long-tail queries.

Chapters 2 through 8 walk through the full operating model: borough-level keyword research across all 44 London boroughs, technical SEO foundations (Core Web Vitals, schema, INP), the GEO framework for engineering content that AI models want to cite, link building from UK authority sources (.gov.uk, .ac.uk, national media), and a measurement approach tied to revenue rather than vanity traffic.

Chapters 9 through 12 are templates you can use today: a 90-day editorial calendar with topic clusters pre-mapped, a monthly SEO reporting dashboard template, outreach scripts for UK journalists and associations, and a full 12-month SEO roadmap for London businesses at every stage — from £0 MRR pre-launch through £5M+ ARR scaleups. The final chapter lists the exact tool stack we use internally, with pricing and substitutes at every tier.
